---
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Modal from "../../components/Modal.astro";
import { siteConfig, pageAssetUrl } from "../../config/site";
import { landingContent } from "../../data/locales";

const content = landingContent.en;
const routePath = "/blog/how-to-study-while-working-full-time/";
const heroImage = pageAssetUrl(routePath, "assets/card-1.png");
---

<PageLayout
  title="How to Study While Working Full Time — Fluxo"
  description="You want to learn something new. A language, a skill, a subject that matters for your career or just for you. And you have maybe 45 minutes a day, if everything goes right."
  canonicalPath="/blog/how-to-study-while-working-full-time/"
  routePath={routePath}
  lang="en"
>
  <Header content={content} routePath={routePath} />

  <main class="article-page">
    <article class="article">

      <div class="article-header">
        <p class="article-category">Knowledge Hub</p>
        <h1 class="article-title">How to Study While Working Full Time?</h1>
        <p class="article-subtitle">You want to learn something new. A language, a skill, a subject that matters for your career or just for you. And you have maybe 45 minutes a day, if everything goes right.</p>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span>Fluxo Team</span>
          <span class="article-meta-dot">·</span>
          <span>5 min read</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="article-hero">
        <img src={heroImage} alt="How to study while working full time" />
      </div>

      <div class="article-body">

        <p>That's actually enough. But only if you use it differently than students do.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>The Wrong Model</h2>

        <p>Most study advice is built for students with four-hour blocks, exam deadlines, and learning as a primary job. When you're working full time, that model doesn't just fail — it sets you up to feel like you're always behind.</p>

        <p>Trying to recreate a student schedule in the gaps of an adult life usually means one focused weekend attempt followed by two weeks of nothing. The inconsistency kills retention faster than any lack of talent.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>Why Shorter, More Frequent Sessions Work Better</h2>

        <p>The research on this is direct. <a href="https://www.yorku.ca/ncepeda/publications/CPVWR2006.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cepeda et al.'s 2006 meta-analysis</a> in <em>Psychological Bulletin</em> showed that distributing learning across multiple sessions produces better retention than the same total time spent in a single sitting. This isn't just a convenience — it's a structural advantage for people with limited daily windows.</p>

        <p>Short daily sessions also match how memory consolidation works. Sleep processes and reinforces what you learned during the day. If you study for 20 minutes tonight and sleep, your brain will work on that material while you rest. Seven 20-minute sessions across a week will produce better retention than one 140-minute session on Saturday.</p>

        <p>This approach even has a name in learning research: microlearning. A <a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2025.1491265/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener">review published in <em>Frontiers in Psychology</em> (2025)</a> found microlearning effective for developing knowledge and skills in time-constrained contexts — exactly the situation of working professionals.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>A Realistic Daily Structure</h2>

        <p><strong>10 to 15 minutes in the morning:</strong> Spaced repetition review. Go through what Fluxo or your app says is due. This catches material before it fades and works with the memory consolidation that happened overnight.</p>

        <p><strong>20 to 30 minutes in the evening:</strong> One focused learning session. New material, reading with active annotation, or working through a concept. No multitasking. Notifications off.</p>

        <p>That's it. 30 to 45 minutes total, no large blocks required.</p>

        <p>The key is protecting those two windows. Not expanding them — protecting them. Consistency over volume.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>The System Matters More Than Motivation</h2>

        <p>The hardest part of studying while working full time isn't finding time. It's making sure that the time you do find is used on the right things. Without a system telling you what to review and what to learn next, you default to starting over, covering the same ground, or just reading passively.</p>

        <p><strong><a href="/">Fluxo</a></strong> gives working learners a system that runs itself. You add what you're learning, the AI generates summaries so you spend less time understanding and more time training, and every day Fluxo shows you exactly what to review in the time you have.</p>

        <p>You don't need hours. You need a system that works in minutes.</p>

        <button type="button" class="btn-primary" data-modal-open data-from="article-cta">Start for free</button>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer content={content} routePath={routePath} />
  <Modal content={content} />
</PageLayout>

<script define:vars={{ leadsUrl: `${siteConfig.leadsApiUrl}/leads`, applicationId: siteConfig.applicationId, toast: landingContent.en.toast }}>
  (() => {
    const modal = document.querySelector("[data-lead-modal]");
    const toastEl = document.querySelector("[data-lead-toast]");
    let toastTimer, lastFocused = null;

    const showToast = (message, isError) => {
      if (!toastEl) return;
      toastEl.textContent = message;
      toastEl.classList.toggle("lead-toast--error", Boolean(isError));
      toastEl.hidden = false;
      void toastEl.offsetWidth;
      toastEl.classList.add("lead-toast--visible");
      clearTimeout(toastTimer);
      toastTimer = setTimeout(() => {
        toastEl.classList.remove("lead-toast--visible");
        setTimeout(() => { toastEl.hidden = true; }, 300);
      }, 4000);
    };

    const openModal = (from) => {
      if (!modal) return;
      const form = modal.querySelector("[data-lead-form]");
      if (form && from) form.setAttribute("data-from", from);
      lastFocused = document.activeElement;
      modal.hidden = false;
      void modal.offsetWidth;
      modal.classList.add("lead-modal--open");
      document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
      const input = modal.querySelector("input");
      if (input) setTimeout(() => input.focus(), 50);
    };

    const closeModal = () => {
      if (!modal) return;
      modal.classList.remove("lead-modal--open");
      document.body.style.overflow = "";
      setTimeout(() => { modal.hidden = true; }, 250);
      if (lastFocused && typeof lastFocused.focus === "function") lastFocused.focus();
    };

    document.querySelectorAll("[data-modal-open]").forEach((trigger) => {
      trigger.addEventListener("click", () => openModal(trigger.getAttribute("data-from")));
    });

    if (modal) {
      modal.querySelectorAll("[data-modal-close]").forEach((el) => {
        el.addEventListener("click", closeModal);
      });
    }

    document.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
      if (e.key === "Escape" && modal && !modal.hidden) closeModal();
    });

    document.querySelectorAll("[data-lead-form]").forEach((form) => {
      form.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        const input = form.querySelector('input[type="email"]');
        const button = form.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
        const email = input ? input.value.trim() : "";
        const from = form.getAttribute("data-from") || "unknown";
        if (!input || !input.checkValidity() || !email) { if (input) input.reportValidity(); return; }
        if (button) button.disabled = true;
        form.setAttribute("aria-busy", "true");
        try {
          const res = await fetch(leadsUrl, { method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" }, body: JSON.stringify({ email, applicationId, metadata: { from } }) });
          if (!res.ok) throw new Error();
          if (input) input.value = "";
          if (modal && form.closest("[data-lead-modal]")) closeModal();
          showToast(toast.success, false);
        } catch {
          showToast(toast.error, true);
        } finally {
          if (button) button.disabled = false;
          form.removeAttribute("aria-busy");
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>

<style>
  .article-page {
    padding-top: 80px;
    background: #F3F3F3;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .article {
    max-width: 1192px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 24px 100px;
  }

  /* Header */
  .article-header {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
  }

  .article-category {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .article-title {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 42px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .article-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #3D3D3D;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .article-meta {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .article-meta-dot {
    color: #B0B0B0;
  }

  /* Hero image */
  .article-hero {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto 56px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .article-hero img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    max-height: 520px;
  }

  /* Body */
  .article-body {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .article-body p {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #1C1C1C;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .article-body h2 {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 52px 0 16px;
  }

  .article-body h3 {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 36px 0 12px;
  }

  .article-body strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0E0E0E;
  }

  .article-body em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .article-body a {
    color: #4C27E3;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(76, 39, 227, 0.35);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s;
  }

  .article-body a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: #4C27E3;
  }

  .article-body button.btn-secondary {
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .article-rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #E8E8E8;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .sources-title {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .sources-list {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sources-list li {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .sources-list a {
    color: #6B6B6B;
    font-size: 13px;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article {
      padding: 40px 20px 80px;
    }

    .article-title {
      font-size: 30px;
    }

    .article-subtitle {
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .article-hero {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .article-body p {
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .article-body h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }

    .article-body h3 {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>
